	"assembly": "#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nbookmark Instructions\n\nsub_bookmark Basic\nsymbol nop 0x00000000 # No Operation\nsymbol hlt 0x01000000 # Halt\nsub_bookmark Load/Store\nsymbol lda 0x02000000 # Load A\nsymbol ldb 0x03000000 # Load B\nsymbol lia 0x04000000 # Load Immediate A\nsymbol lib 0x05000000 # Load Immediate B\nsymbol sta 0x06000000 # Store A\nsymbol laa 0x07000000 # Load A from A\nsub_bookmark ALU\nsymbol add 0x08000000 # Add\nsymbol sub 0x09000000 # Subtract\nsymbol inc 0x0a000000 # Increment A\nsymbol dec 0x0b000000 # Decrement A\nsymbol not 0x0c000000 # Not A\nsymbol and 0x0d000000 # And A & B\nsymbol orr 0x0e000000 # Or A & B\nsymbol xor 0x0f000000 # Xor A & B\nsymbol sar 0x10000000 # Shift Arithmetic Right\nsymbol sll 0x11000000 # Shift Logical Left\nsymbol slr 0x12000000 # Shift Logical Right\nsymbol scl 0x13000000 # Shift Circular Left\nsymbol scr 0x14000000 # Shift Circular Right\nsub_bookmark Stack\nsymbol cal 0x15000000 # Call\nsymbol ret 0x16000000 # Return\nsymbol psh 0x17000000 # Push A to Stack\nsymbol pop 0x18000000 # Pop from Stack to A\nsub_bookmark IO\nsymbol gin 0x19000000 # Get Input\nsymbol out 0x1a000000 # Set Output\nsub_bookmark Branching\nsymbol jmp 0x1b000000 # Jump\nsymbol jcr 0x1c000000 # Jump on Carry\nsymbol jne 0x1d000000 # Jump on Negative\nsymbol jnz 0x1e000000 # Jump on Negative or Zero\nsymbol jze 0x1f000000 # Jump on Zero\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nbookmark Constants\n\n# This is needed in a few places since\n# the Load Immediate instructions in this sample\n# computer only support unsigned 24-bit integers.\npointer minus_one inline -1\n\nsymbol end_of_string -1\nsymbol true 1\nsymbol false 0\nsymbol btn_count \t1\nsymbol btn_primes \t2\nsymbol btn_fib \t\t4\nsymbol btn_accept \t8\nsymbol btn_cancel \t16\n\n#-----------------------------\n\nsymbol cA 10\nsymbol cB 11\nsymbol cC 12\nsymbol cD 13\nsymbol cE 14\nsymbol cF 15\nsymbol cG 16\nsymbol cH 17\nsymbol cI 18\nsymbol cJ 19\nsymbol cK 20\nsymbol cL 21\nsymbol cM 22\nsymbol cN 23\nsymbol cO 24\nsymbol cP 25\nsymbol cQ 26\nsymbol cR 27\nsymbol cS 28\nsymbol cT 29\nsymbol cU 30\nsymbol cV 31\nsymbol cW 32\nsymbol cX 33\nsymbol cY 34\nsymbol cZ 35\nsymbol c_ 36\n\n#-----------------------------\n\norigin 10000\n0b11111; 0b10001; 0b11111 # 0\n0b01001; 0b11111; 0b00001 # 1\n0b10111; 0b10101; 0b11101 # 2\n0b10001; 0b10101; 0b11111 # 3\n0b11100; 0b00100; 0b11111 # 4\n0b11101; 0b10101; 0b10111 # 5\n0b11111; 0b10101; 0b10111 # 6\n0b10000; 0b10000; 0b11111 # 7\n0b11111; 0b10101; 0b11111 # 8\n0b11101; 0b10101; 0b11111 # 9\n0b11111; 0b10100; 0b11111 # A\n0b11111; 0b10101; 0b01010 # B\n0b11111; 0b10001; 0b10001 # C\n0b11111; 0b10001; 0b01110 # D\n0b11111; 0b10101; 0b10001 # E\n0b11111; 0b10100; 0b10000 # F\n0b11111; 0b10001; 0b10011 # G\n0b11111; 0b00100; 0b11111 # H\n0b10001; 0b11111; 0b10001 # I\n0b10001; 0b11111; 0b10000 # J\n0b11111; 0b00100; 0b11011 # K\n0b11111; 0b00001; 0b00001 # L\n0b11111; 0b01000; 0b11111 # M\n0b11111; 0b10000; 0b01111 # N\n0b11110; 0b10001; 0b11111 # O\n0b11111; 0b10100; 0b11100 # P\n0b11110; 0b10010; 0b11101 # Q\n0b11111; 0b10100; 0b11011 # R\n0b01101; 0b10101; 0b10110 # S\n0b10000; 0b11111; 0b10000 # T\n0b11111; 0b00001; 0b11111 # U\n0b11110; 0b00001; 0b11110 # V\n0b11111; 0b00010; 0b11111 # W\n0b11011; 0b00100; 0b11011 # X\n0b11000; 0b00111; 0b11000 # Y\n0b10011; 0b10101; 0b11001 # Z\n0b00000; 0b00000; 0b00000 # Space\norigin orgprev\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nmacro printb {lia StringStarta?; psh; cal PrintStringMem; @ StringStarta?; jmp StringEnda?}\nmacro printd {end_of_string; @ StringEnda?}\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nbookmark Boot\n@ Boot\n\thlt; gin\n\tjmp Main\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nbookmark Main\n\tpointer input inline 0\n\n@ Main\n\tcal PrintClear\n\t# Prints \"select a program\".\n\tprintb 0\n\tcS; cE; cL; cE; cC; cT; c_; cA; c_;\n\tcP; cR; cO; cG; cR; cA; cM;\n\tprintd 0\n\thlt\n\n@ MainInput\n\t# Detects which button was pressed and\n\t# jumps to the corresponding program.\n\tgin\n\tsta input\n\tlib btn_count; sub\n\tjze ProgramCount\n\n\tlda input\n\tlib btn_primes; sub\n\tjze ProgramPrimes\n\n\tlda input\n\tlib btn_fib; sub\n\tjze ProgramFibonacci\n\n\thlt\n\tjmp MainInput\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nbookmark Multiply\n\tpointer mplier \tinline 0 \t\t# Multiplier\n\tpointer mcand \tinline 0 \t\t# Multiplicand\n\tpointer product inline 0\n\tpointer\tcount\tinline 0\n\n@ Multiply # (mplier, mcand)\n\t# Stack is inverted.\n\tpop; sta mcand\n\tpop; sta mplier\n\tlia 0; sta product;\n\tlia 33; sta count;\n\n@ Multiply1\n\tlda count; lib 1; sub\n\tjze MultiplyReturn\n\tsta count\n\t# Masks only the first bit of the\n\t# Multiplier and sets flags.\n\tlda mplier\t\t\t\t\n\tlib 1\n\tand\t\t\n\n\t# If Multiplier is not 0 then adds the\n\t# Multiplicand to the Product.\n\tjze Multiply2\n\tlda product\n\tldb mcand\n\tadd\n\tsta product\n\n@ Multiply2\n\t# Shifts Multiplicand left and Multiplier right.\n\tlda mcand\n\tsll\n\tsta mcand\n\tlda mplier\n\tslr\n\tsta mplier\n\tjmp Multiply1\n\n@ MultiplyReturn\n\tlda product; psh\n\tret\n\n\tunpoint mplier\n\tunpoint mcand\n\tunpoint product\n\tunpoint\tcount\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nbookmark Divide\n# Binary division by shift and subtract.\n\n\t# We need two variables to hold the dividend\n\t# since this sample computer uses a 32-bit ALU.\n\tpointer dividend \tinline 0\n\tpointer ddend \t\tinline 0\n\tpointer dvsor \t\tinline 0\n\tpointer quotient \tinline 0\n\tpointer count \t\tinline 0\n\n@ Divide # (dividend, divisor)\n\tlia 0; sta ddend; sta quotient\n\tlia 33; sta count;\n\t# Stack is inverted.\n\tpop; sta dvsor\n\tpop; sta dividend\n\n@ Divide1\n\t# Takes 33 cycles.\n\tlda count; lib 1; sub\n\tjze DivideReturn\n\tsta count\n\t\n\tlda quotient\n\n\t# Takes the next least-significant bit from the original\n\t# dividend and concatenates to the right of the working\n\t# dividend. Basically emulates the behavior of a left\n\t# shift in a 64-bit ALU.\n\tlda ddend\n\tsll\n\tsta ddend\n\tlda dividend\n\tscl\n\tsta dividend\n\tlib 1\n\tand\n\tldb ddend\n\torr\n\tsta ddend\n\n\t# Is the portion of the ddend >= dvsor?\n\tldb dvsor\n\tsub\n\tjne Divide2\n\n\t# YES\n\t# The (ddend - dvsor) subtraction is kept.\n\tsta ddend\n\t# Concatenates 1 to the right of the quotient.\n\tlda quotient\n\tsll\n\tlib 1\n\torr\n\tsta quotient\n\tjmp Divide1\n\n\t# NO\n\t@ Divide2\n\t# Concatenates 0 to the right of the quotient.\n\tlda quotient\n\tsll\n\tsta quotient\n\tjmp Divide1\n\n@ DivideReturn\n\tlda ddend\n\tpsh\n\tlda quotient\n\tpsh\n\tret\n\n\tunpoint dividend\n\tunpoint ddend\n\tunpoint dvsor\n\tunpoint quotient\n\tunpoint count\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nbookmark Print\nsub_bookmark Char\n\tpointer char inline 0\n\n@ PrintChar # (char)\n\tlia 0; sta char\n\n\tpop\n\tsta char\n\tldb char\n\tadd\n\tadd\n\n\tlib 10000\n\tadd\n\tsta char\n\n\tlaa\n\tout\n\n\tlda char\n\tinc\n\tlaa\n\tout\n\n\tlda char\n\tinc\n\tinc\n\tlaa\n\tout\n\n\tlia 0\n\tout\n\n\tret\n\n\tunpoint char\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nsub_bookmark StringStack\n@ PrintStringStack # (string)\n\tpop\n\tjne PrintStringStackEnd\n\tpsh\n\tcal PrintChar\n\tjmp PrintStringStack\n\n@ PrintStringStackEnd\n\tret\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nsub_bookmark StringMem\n\tpointer address inline 0\n\n@ PrintStringMem # (address)\n\tpop; sta address\n\n@ PrintStringMem1\n\tlda address\n\tlib 1; add\n\tsta address\n\tlaa\n\tjne PrintStringReturn\n\tpsh\n\tcal PrintChar\n\tjmp PrintStringMem1\n\n@ PrintStringReturn\n\tret\n\n\tunpoint address\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nsub_bookmark Decimal\n\tpointer is_clear inline 0\n\tpointer quotient inline 0\n\tpointer remainder inline 0\t\n\n@ PrintDecimal # (binary_value, is_clear)\n\tpop; sta is_clear\n\tpop; sta quotient\n\tlia 0; sta remainder\n\t# Indicates the end of chars on the stack.\n\tlda minus_one; psh \n\n@ PrintDecimal1\n\tlda quotient; psh\n\tlia 10; psh\n\tcal Divide\n\tpop # Pops quotient\n\tsta quotient\n\tpop # Pops remainder\n\tsta remainder\n\tpsh # Decimal char is added to the stack.\n\tlda quotient\n\tjnz PrintDecimal2\n\tjmp PrintDecimal1\n\n@ PrintDecimal2 # Clear true\n\tlda is_clear\n\tjze PrintDecimal3\n\tcal PrintClear\n\tcal PrintStringStack\n\tjmp PrintDecimalReturn\n\n@ PrintDecimal3 # Clear false\n\tcal PrintStringStack\n\tjmp PrintDecimalReturn\n\n@ PrintDecimalReturn\n\tret\n\n\tunpoint is_clear\n\tunpoint quotient\n\tunpoint remainder\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nsub_bookmark Blank\n\tpointer count inline 0\n\n@ PrintBlank # (amount + 1)\n\tpop; sta count\n\tlib 1; sub\n\tsta count\n\tjze PrintBlankReturn\n\tout\n\tjmp PrintBlank\n\n@ PrintBlankReturn\n\tret\n\n\tunpoint count\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nsub_bookmark Clear\n@ PrintClear\n\tlia 32\n\tout\n\tret\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nbookmark Programs\nsub_bookmark Count\n\tpointer count inline 0\n\n@ ProgramCount\n\tcal PrintClear\n\tlia 0; sta count\n\n\tlda minus_one; psh\n\tlia cD; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cT; psh\n\tlia cC; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cL; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cS; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tlia cT; psh\n\tlia cN; psh\n\tlia cU; psh\n\tlia cO; psh\n\tlia cC; psh\n\tcal PrintStringStack\n\thlt; gin\n\tcal PrintClear\n\n@ ProgramCount1\n\tlda count\n\tinc\n\tsta count\n\tpsh\n\tlia true; psh\n\tcal PrintDecimal\n\n\t# Get Input\n\tgin\n\tlib btn_cancel; sub\n\tjze ProgramCountReturn\n\n\tjmp ProgramCount1\n\n@ ProgramCountReturn\n\tcal PrintClear\n\tjmp Main\n\n\tunpoint count\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nsub_bookmark Fibonacci\n\tpointer sum inline 0\n\tpointer temp inline 0\n\tpointer prev inline 0\n\n@ ProgramFibonacci\n\tcal PrintClear\n\tlia 0; sta temp; sta prev\n\tlia 1; sta sum\n\n\tlda minus_one; psh\n\tlia cD; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cT; psh\n\tlia cC; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cL; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cS; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tlia cI; psh\n\tlia cC; psh\n\tlia cC; psh\n\tlia cA; psh\n\tlia cN; psh\n\tlia cO; psh\n\tlia cB; psh\n\tlia cI; psh\n\tlia cF; psh\n\tcal PrintStringStack\n\thlt; gin\n\tcal PrintClear\n\n@ ProgramFibonacci1\t\n\tlda sum\n\tsta temp\t# temp = sum\n\tldb prev\n\tadd\t\t\t# sum += prev\n\tjcr ProgramFibonacciReset\n\tsta sum\n\tlda temp\n\tsta prev\t# prev = temp\n\n\tlda sum; psh\n\tlia true; psh\n\tcal PrintDecimal\n\n\t# Input\n\tgin\n\tlib btn_cancel; sub\n\tjze ProgramFibonacciReturn\n\n\tjmp ProgramFibonacci1\n\n@ ProgramFibonacciReset\n\tlia 0; sta temp; sta prev\n\tlia 1; sta sum\n\tjmp ProgramFibonacci1\n\t\n@ ProgramFibonacciReturn\n\tcal PrintClear\n\tjmp Main\n\n\tunpoint sum\n\tunpoint temp\n\tunpoint prev\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------\n\nsub_bookmark Primes\n\tpointer n inline 0\n\tpointer i inline 0\n\tpointer ra inline 0\n\n@ ProgramPrimes\n\tcal PrintClear\n\tlia 4; sta n # 1, 2, and 3 are hardcoded exceptions.\n\tlia 5; sta i\n\tlia 0; sta ra\n\n\tlda minus_one; psh\n\tlia cD; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cT; psh\n\tlia cC; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cL; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cS; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tlia cS; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cM; psh\n\tlia cI; psh\n\tlia cR; psh\n\tlia cP; psh\n\tcal PrintStringStack\n\thlt; gin\n\tcal PrintClear\n\n@ ProgramPrimes1\n\tlia 2; psh\n\tcal PrintChar\n\tcal ProgramPrimesIsPrime\n\tgin\n\tcal PrintClear\n\tlia 3; psh\n\tcal PrintChar\n\tcal ProgramPrimesIsPrime\n\tjmp ProgramPrimes2\n\n@ ProgramPrimesIsPrime\n\tlda minus_one; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cM; psh\n\tlia cI; psh\n\tlia cR; psh\n\tlia cP; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tlia cS; psh\n\tlia cI; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tcal PrintStringStack\n\thlt\t\n\tret\n\n@ ProgramPrimesIsComposite\n\tlda minus_one; psh\n\tlia cE; psh\n\tlia cT; psh\n\tlia cI; psh\n\tlia cS; psh\n\tlia cO; psh\n\tlia cP; psh\n\tlia cM; psh\n\tlia cO; psh\n\tlia cC; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tlia cS; psh\n\tlia cI; psh\n\tlia c_; psh\n\tcal PrintStringStack\n\thlt\t\n\tret\n\n@ ProgramPrimes2\n\tgin\n\tsta input\n\tlib btn_cancel; sub\n\tjze ProgramPrimesReturn\n\n\tlda input\n\tlib btn_accept; sub\n\tjze ProgramPrimes3\n\n\thlt\n\tjmp ProgramPrimes2\n\n@ ProgramPrimes3\n\tlia 5; sta i\n\tlda n; psh\n\tlia 2; psh\n\tcal Divide\n\tpop # Pops quotient\n\tpop # Pops remainder\n\tjze ProgramPrimesFalse\n\t#\n\tlda n; psh\n\tlia 3; psh\n\tcal Divide\n\tpop # Pops quotient\n\tpop # Pops remainder\n\tjze ProgramPrimesFalse\n\n@ ProgramPrimesLoop\n\tlda i; psh; psh\n\tcal Multiply\n\tpop\n\tldb n\n\tsub\n\tjnz ProgramPrimesLoop1 # (n <= i)\n\tjmp ProgramPrimesTrue\n\n@ ProgramPrimesLoop1\n\tlda n; psh\n\tlda i; psh\n\tcal Divide\n\tpop # Pops quotient\n\tpop # Pops remainder\n\tjze ProgramPrimesFalse\n\t#\n\tlda i; inc; inc; sta ra\n\tlda n; psh\n\tlda ra; psh\n\tcal Divide\n\tpop # Pops quotient\n\tpop # Pops remainder\n\tjze ProgramPrimesFalse\n\t#\n\tlda i\n\tlib 6\n\tadd\n\tsta i\n\tjmp ProgramPrimesLoop\n\n@ ProgramPrimesFalse\n\tlda n; psh\n\tlia true; psh\n\tcal PrintDecimal\n\tcal ProgramPrimesIsComposite\n\tlda n; inc; sta n\n\tjmp ProgramPrimes2\n\n@ ProgramPrimesTrue\n\tlda n; psh\n\tlia true; psh\n\tcal PrintDecimal\n\tcal ProgramPrimesIsPrime\n\tlda n; inc; sta n\n\tjmp ProgramPrimes2\n\n@ ProgramPrimesReturn\n\tcal PrintClear\n\tjmp Main\n\n\tunpoint n\n\tunpoint i\n\tunpoint ra\n\n#-----------------------------------------------------------",
	"is_vmem_enabled": true,
